comment:
* Object used to report back gesture progress. Holds information about a {@link BackEvent} plus
 * any {@link RemoteAnimationTarget} the gesture manipulates.
 *
 * @see BackEvent
 * @hide

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
public float getTouchX()
methods.comment: * Returns the absolute X location of the touch point.

methods.name: public float getTouchY()
methods.comment: * Returns the absolute Y location of the touch point.

methods.name: public float getProgress()
methods.comment:
* Returns the progress of a {@link BackEvent}.
     *
     * @see BackEvent#getProgress()

methods.name: public float getVelocityX()
methods.comment:
* Returns the X velocity computed from the touch point.
     *
     * @return value in pixels/second or {@link Float#NaN} if was not computed.

methods.name: public float getVelocityY()
methods.comment:
* Returns the Y velocity computed from the touch point.
     *
     * @return value in pixels/second or {@link Float#NaN} if was not computed.

methods.name: public boolean getTriggerBack()
methods.comment:
* Returns whether the back arrow is in the triggered state or not
     *
     * @return boolean indicating whether the back arrow is in the triggered state or not

methods.name: public int getSwipeEdge()
methods.comment: * Returns the screen edge that the swipe starts from.

methods.name: public RemoteAnimationTarget getDepartingAnimationTarget()
methods.comment:
* Returns the {@link RemoteAnimationTarget} of the top departing application window,
     * or {@code null} if the top window should not be moved for the current type of back
     * destination.

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
